<section class="content-container judge">

      <article>
        <%=link_to 'See the list of all judges', judges_path, class: 'pull-right orange-link' %>
        <h2>Judging Paradigm</h2>
        <h3 class="subheader"><%= image_tag @judge.user.image%><%= @judge.user.name%></h3>
        <% unless @judge.experience.blank? %>
            <header>Experience</header>
            <ul>
              <% for experience in @judge.experience.split(',') %>
              <li><b><%=experience%></b>.</li>
              <% end %>
              <li>Has been judging debate for <b><%=@judge.years_judging || '__'%></b> years.</li>
              <li>Judged <b><%=@judge.season_judged_no || '__' %></b> rounds this season so far.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="comments"><%=@judge.experience_comments%></div>
      <% end %>
        <header>Delivery</header>
        <ul>
          <li>On a scale from 1 (slow conversational style) to 4 (typical conversational speed) to 7 (rapid conversational speed), I prefer a <b><%=@judge.delivery_preference || "___"%></b> out of 7.</li>
          <li>The rate of delivery <b><%= ("does" if @judge.delivery_weight == "Yes") || ("does not" if @judge.delivery_weight == "No") || "___" %></b> weight heavily in my decision.</li>
          <li>I <b><%= ("will" if @judge.delivery_dealbreaker == "Yes") || ("will not" if @judge.delivery_dealbreaker == "No") || "___" %></b> vote against a student solely for exceeding my preferred speed.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="comments"><%=@judge.delivery_comments%></div>
        <header>Criterion</header>
        <ul>
          <li>The criterion <b><%= @judge.criterion_weight.sub("It ","") || "___" %></b></li>
          <li>I feel that a value and criterion are <b><%= ("required" if @judge.criterion_required == "Yes") || ("not required" if @judge.criterion_required == "No") || "___" %></b> elements of a case.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="comments"><%=@judge.criterion_comments%></div>

        <header>Rebuttals and Crystallization</header>
        <ul>
          <li>Final rebuttals should include <b><%=@judge.final_rebuttals_should_include || "___" %></b>.</li>
          <li>Voting issues should be given <b><%=@judge.voting_issues_necessity || "___" %></b></li>
          <li>Voting issues are <b><%=@judge.voting_issues_are || "___" %>.</b></li>
          <li>The use of jargon or technical language ("extend", "cross-apply", "turn", etc.) during rebuttal is <b><%=@judge.jargon_preference || "___" %></b>.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="comments"><%=@judge.rebuttal_comments%></div>

        <header>Decision-Making</header>
        <ul>
          <li>In deciding the winner of the round, <b><%= @judge.decision_paradigm%></b></li>
          <li>On a scale of 1 (not necessary) to 4 (sometimes necessary) to 7 (always necesary), I feel that the use of evidence (both analytical and empirical) in the round is a <b><%= @judge.evidence_necessity || "___" %></b> out of 7.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="comments"><%=@judge.decision_comments%></div>

        <header>Note-taking</header>
        <ul>
          <li>During the round, <b><%=@judge.notetaking_preference || "___" %></b></li>
        </ul>
        <div class="comments"><%=@judge.notetaking_comments%></div>

        <header>Additional</header>
        <div class="comments">
          <%= simple_format(@judge.paradigm) %>
        </div>
        <br><br><br>
        <%=link_to 'See the list of all judges', judges_path, class: 'pull-right orange-link' %>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>